qas.question: Who showed up on the editorial floor of the Independent?
Who was the editor of the Independent?
What did The Sun neglect to report concerning the upcoming election?
Who did the Independent state wouldn't decide the election?
What year was the United Kingdom general election?

context: During the campaign for the United Kingdom general election, <a4_0>2010<a4_0/>, The Independent ran ads declaring that "<a3_0>Rupert Murdoch<a3_0/> won't decide this election – you will." In response <a0_0>James Murdoch and Rebekah Wade<a0_0/> "appeared unannounced and uninvited on the editorial floor" of the Independent, and had an energetic conversation with its editor <a1_0>Simon Kelner<a1_0/>. Several days later the Independent reported The Sun's failure to report <a2_0>its own YouGov poll result<a2_0/> which said that "if people thought Mr Clegg's party had a significant chance of winning the election" the Liberal Democrats would win 49% of the vote, and with it a landslide majority.
